			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">what ARE people doing?<a name="45162"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 9 04 1:54 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>so i consider myself a decent bard. with quite a bit of experience playing at the lower - mid levels (I have a 22 bard on vazaelle, a 52 bard on FV, and a 56 bard on Mith Marr, and have been playing the game 5+ years now, tho my main is a paladin).
<br />

<br />
but I dont consider myself a jaw-droppingly good bard, competent I hope and always finding new things to learn.
<br />

<br />
Seems every time I group someone sends me a tell how good I am.
<br />

<br />
Ok maybe in LDON where I'm chain pulling singles and stuff, I do think I'm a decent puller.  Though I always seem to get at least a couple messy pulls per adventure, but hey that just livens things up right? hehe.
<br />

<br />
But last night I joined a group in progress.  The ranger was already pulling, we had a shaman slowing and hasting, and so I decided to just twist three songs and melee. Later after the ranger left I pulled,... Note, the ranger had no problem getting singles most of the time, and neither did I...
<br />

<br />
So I'm mostly standing around, self-indulgently playing Kattas since I need melee skill ups, heh, and twisting mana and Erjav's, occasionally (and I mean very occasionally) mezzing or charming nearby pops.
<br />

<br />
I start getting tells about how I'm a fantastic bard, etc.
<br />

<br />
What ARE folks doing ? I mean, I wasn't doing ANYTHING special. In fact I was feeling lazy and self indulgent! 
<br />

<br />
It was just kind of funny.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
