			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what ARE people doing?<a name="45179"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 9 04 3:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm guilty of complaining to bards about not singing enough songs when they are doing more than I noticed.
<br />

<br />
I sometimes find my alts in a group with a bard and only see 1 maybe 2 icons in my buff window max, I tend to think that the bard is being lazy or is a one-hit wonder. But then I notice &quot;a Picklaw Guard is surrounded by chains of music&quot;  and I realize hes been slowing/snaring the whole time /bonk. If a person with a bard main can sometimes not notice how much work a bard is putting forth, I'm certain non-bard players would be even more likely to not see it. They only see whats in their buff window and sometimes feel thats enough to compliment/vilify the bard. 
<br />

<br />
Also, I've met some people who just don't understand how bards work and thus don't know that what a bard has done is anything out of the ordinary.
<br />

<br />
Take mezzing, enchanters can lock down 4 5 mobs without batting an eyelash. Because of that most people assume bards are the same, mezz and forget. They just don't realize we're moving all over the place twisting one mezz after another trying to keep up retargeting the next mob all the while remembering which order we mezzed them and trying to becareful which way mezz push will land. During this time, I have no beneficial songs to please their buff window, I have gotten vilified for not hasting and &quot;singing mana&quot; during such a situation. Lazy bard, right?
<br />

<br />
I get complimented infrequently regarding my 4 song twists. I nod a thank you but I don't feel special(being complimented for twisting is like complimenting a cleric for medding). Its kind of saddening that I'd get complimented for just twisting. The most gratifying compliments are those that aim more at my contributions to group play, or when people ask to put me on friends lists, that always puts a smile on my face and make the last hour or so of non-stop twisting and vigilance worth it. 
<br />

<br />
Repeat customers is teh bestest.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
