				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what ARE people doing?<a name="45180"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 9 04 3:22 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have a 65 beastlord and a 65 bard (main) and I have been in both situations where I considered a bard to be a good one and ones that are worthless.
<br />

<br />
Since I am very familiar with what a bard can do with bad pulls or mezzing I still get shocked when I see a bard pull, gets two, and then proceeds to only mez the add and not play a single other song. And no, before people say &quot;maybe they were getting high resists on the mez when they do that&quot; it is EVERY time they have an extra mob in camp. Having done enough normal LDoN (where this occurs) I can say for sure they are either lazy or do not understand what they are/should/could be doing.
<br />

<br />
However I have also been in with bards that do a good job, keep some haste and mana while still mezzing an add and snaring, things most can and will do. I keep my filters set so that I see bard songs in group that way if I am not on my bard I do not think lazy or worthless when I can see all messages related to what they are doing.
<br />

<br />
What you are doing is most likely the normal, there are just so many out there that do not understand what a bard can do that they do so little and the normal shines. If that makes any sense.</span></td>
