				<td colspan="2"><span>You know, I'm not lazy. I always keep a 4 twist up, I rarely overpull and I'm never sloppy on timing. The other night, I had this lady completely bitch me out in tells about how I should be twisting if I only have 1 add. Should? Piss off. I work my a$ off man, and I always keep slow and snare going on adds, sometimes OoS if I can throw it in too. If I do my job right, I don't NEED to twist mana song and ds while I mez, because I won't have to mez at all. You'll rarely see me have to mez, and if you do, you won't see overhaste in your window, just a little dark blue message that slips into your battle spam and you never really notice it. You know the old saying &quot;We the underappreciated have been doing so much with so little for so long that we can now do almost anything with absolutely nothing.&quot; That's being a bard, and being a bard is also about not giving a crap what other people think, and never asking for gratitude. 
<br />

<br />
But I swear, if someone patronizes me......
<br />
Maybe that's just me man, I have a fierce sense of pride in what I do, whether someone notices it or not, and I don't care if I do it as well or better than most bards, I get the job done, always.
